$interpreted: Leah: Whew~ that was exhausting...if I knew it was this much of a hassle, I wouldn't have come back for those three idiots...
Leah: Good thing that I still have the Tana Root with me. Gotta get back to Rune Academy now and finish the job!
Leah: Oh...umm, hi there, long time no see?
Leah: ...I-I finally... won...need... to get back...to the Rune....
Leah: ... Crap, can't even move a muscle now...
Leah: ... If only I took the root back myself...I wonder if those three idiots made it back to the Academy safely?
Leah: They're probably in a warm bath, sipping on some cold drinks by now...
Annie: To protect the freshman from devastation!
Betty: To unite the people within our nation!
Cara: That's right~~ Eat this, stupid monster!
Leah: Headmaster Ceres, the seniors and I have brought the Tana Root back together.
Annie: We would like headmaster to revoke our expulsions!
Charle: So, you finally made it back? This is the last ingredient I need to complete my cake.
Leah: Cake!?
Charle: Yes. Sprinkling some ground Tana Root on the cake gives it a nice smell~
Betty: So it's a food ingredient, not a rune material!
Leah: We literally almost died trying to find it!
Cara: So, when do we get to eat the cake?
Charle: You ladies seem much closer to each other now.
Charle: Then give me a moment. I'll treat you to the cake I just made. Take it as an apology for not explaining things clearly before.
Leah: ...Thank you all for coming back for me...
Annie: ... You came to the cave to rescue us as well. We're even.
Leah: But I purposely led you guys down the wrong path in the forest...
Betty: We also pushed you over before that. We should be the ones apologizing.
Leah: That time in the hallway, it was me who sneak-attacked you with Rune magic...

Cara: We were at fault for making fun of you first. It's ok.
By the way, can you teach us the Rune magic you used back then? It's pretty impressive.
Leah: Hmm, the scent of the cake. It smells really good!
Annie: Really? I haven't smelled anything. Your nose really is amazing!
Leah: If not for you three coming back for me, I would've been long dead. For that reason, you guys can have my share of headmaster's cake!
Annie: You don't have to be so modest.
Leah: No, I owe my life to you guys. I insist that you eat my portion.
Betty: Isn't that a bit unfair?
Cara: But to be honest, I am a little hungry. I wouldn't mind a larger piece...
Leah: Then take it. I don't mind missing out on the cake this time!
Annie: If that's the case... I guess we gladly accept it. Thank you.
Charle: Here comes the cake!
Cara: W-What the hell is this monstrosity? Why does this "cake" smell so bad~
Betty: Didn't he say that sprinkling Tana Root on would make the cake smell nice? Where did that go!
Annie: I thought demihumans had a good nose? Then why did Leah...
Annie: Wait, could it be!
Leah: Headmaster Ceres, just now, I promised to give my share to the seniors as a sign of my gratitude for them saving my life.
Leah: They accepted it with glee.
Charle: It pleases me greatly to see that you ladies have become such close friends. Since that's the case, feel free to have extra, ladies.
Charle: Here you go. I've tried it; it's really delicious~
Annie: What do you mean "You've tried it"? Is this even edible!?
Betty: So the rumors are true...Headmaster Charle really does have some messed up taste buds...
Cara: ...*gag*... Mama, help~
Leah: Hehehehe.
